- [ ] **CHK104** - Are tooltip/help text requirements specified for complex widget configurations? [Usability, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK105** - Are onboarding/tutorial requirements defined for first-time dashboard creators? [Usability, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK106** - Are notification requirements specified for background widget refresh completion? [Usability, Gap]

### Maintainability Requirements

- [ ] **CHK107** - Are requirements defined for dashboard configuration schema versioning? [Maintainability, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK108** - Are migration requirements specified for updating existing dashboards after schema changes? [Maintainability, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK109** - Are logging requirements defined for debugging widget data fetch failures? [Maintainability, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK110** - Are requirements specified for exporting dashboard audit logs? [Maintainability, Gap]

## Dependencies & Assumptions

### External Dependencies

- [ ] **CHK111** - Are requirements specified for validating the "existing system API endpoints remain available" assumption? [Dependency, Spec §Assumptions]
- [ ] **CHK112** - Are requirements defined for handling breaking changes in external API responses? [Dependency, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK113** - Are requirements specified for monitoring dashboard framework dependencies on system infrastructure? [Dependency, Gap]

### Data Format Assumptions

- [ ] **CHK114** - Is the "all API endpoints return JSON" assumption validated against all system endpoints? [Assumption, Spec §Assumptions]
- [ ] **CHK115** - Are requirements defined for handling non-JSON API responses gracefully? [Assumption, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK116** - Are requirements specified for data schema validation before widget processing? [Assumption, Gap]

### Performance Assumptions

- [ ] **CHK117** - Is the "2 seconds for 10K records" assumption validated with actual system data? [Assumption, Spec §Assumptions]
- [ ] **CHK118** - Are requirements defined for widgets handling datasets exceeding performance assumptions? [Assumption, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK119** - Are requirements specified for adaptive performance tuning based on client capabilities? [Assumption, Gap]

### Browser Support Assumptions

- [ ] **CHK120** - Is the "2-year modern browser" assumption compatible with actual user base browser distribution? [Assumption, Spec §Assumptions]
- [ ] **CHK121** - Are requirements defined for feature detection and polyfills for older browsers? [Assumption, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK122** - Are requirements specified for warning users about unsupported browsers? [Assumption, Gap]

## Ambiguities & Conflicts

### Term Definition Issues

- [ ] **CHK123** - Is "widget type" consistently defined across spec (FR-001 mentions 5 types, but are there more)? [Ambiguity]
- [ ] **CHK124** - Is "dashboard template" distinct from "dashboard configuration" with clear definitions? [Ambiguity]
- [ ] **CHK125** - Is "calculation pipeline" implementation-agnostic or does it prescribe specific order? [Ambiguity, Spec §FR-010]
- [ ] **CHK126** - Is "global filter" scope unambiguous (all widgets, or only compatible widgets)? [Ambiguity]

### Requirement Conflicts

- [ ] **CHK127** - Do refresh interval requirements conflict between user stories (60 sec) and FR-004 (30-60 min)? [Conflict, Spec §FR-004]
- [ ] **CHK128** - Do widget independence requirements (FR-002) conflict with global filter requirements (FR-018)? [Conflict]
- [ ] **CHK129** - Do browser storage assumptions conflict with "stored server-side" for cross-device access? [Conflict, Spec §Assumptions]

### Scope Boundary Issues

- [ ] **CHK130** - Are requirements explicitly excluding widget template marketplace or community sharing? [Scope, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK131** - Are requirements explicitly excluding real-time collaborative dashboard editing? [Scope, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK132** - Are requirements explicitly excluding dashboard scheduling/automation features? [Scope, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK133** - Are requirements explicitly excluding dashboard embedding in external applications? [Scope, Gap]

## Traceability & Documentation

### Requirement Traceability

- [ ] **CHK134** - Are all 35 functional requirements traceable to at least one user story? [Traceability]
- [ ] **CHK135** - Are all success criteria traceable to specific functional requirements? [Traceability]
- [ ] **CHK136** - Are all edge cases traceable to requirements they extend? [Traceability]
- [ ] **CHK137** - Is a requirement ID scheme established for future requirement additions? [Traceability]

### Documentation Completeness

- [ ] **CHK138** - Are glossary definitions provided for domain-specific terms (widget, calculation pipeline, dashboard)? [Documentation, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK139** - Are user persona details documented beyond role titles (experience level, goals, pain points)? [Documentation, Gap]
- [ ] **CHK140** - Are data flow diagrams or visual specifications referenced for complex interactions? [Documentation, Gap]

---

**Checklist Summary**:
- **Total Items**: 140
- **Focus Areas**: Completeness (40%), Clarity (20%), Consistency (10%), Coverage (20%), NFRs (10%)
- **Gaps Identified**: 85 items marked with [Gap]
- **Ambiguities**: 15 items marked with [Ambiguity]
- **Conflicts**: 3 items marked with [Conflict]
- **Traceability**: 137/140 items (98%) include spec section references or gap markers

**Next Steps**:
1. Review and resolve all [Gap] items by adding missing requirements to spec.md
2. Clarify all [Ambiguity] items with specific, measurable definitions
3. Resolve all [Conflict] items by aligning contradictory requirements
4. After resolution, re-validate with `/speckit.checklist`
